  "body": "Follow on the reviews on the initial PRs [#5754](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/5754), [#6011](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/6011), [#5910](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/5910), [#6157](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/6157)\r\n\r\n- [ ] One CMakeLists.txt per target (add sources at the end using `target_sources` or in a `src.cmake` file)\r\n- [ ] Change public target sources to private and use the `target_include_directories` for specifying headers\r\n- [ ] Remove Qt dependency from StatusGoQt (rename into StatusGoCpp)\r\n- [ ] Add `Status` folder for includes. Add `App`/`Application` for the application namespace\r\n- [ ] Remove usage of `${PROJECT_NAME}` as target name in CMake\r\n- [ ] Decide if we want to switch to `Separate Header Placement`\r\nMaybe save the user's ability to access private headers/sources with `private/` subdirectory or other kind of prefix (e.g. even go Qt-way and create separate private targets in cmake, but this sounds like overkill)\r\n- [ ] Rename `ChatOrWalletAccount ` as `DerivedStatusAccounts`",
